<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 08 at 2:48PM CDT until June 08 at 3:15PM CDT by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 315 PM CDT
FOR NORTHEASTERN SHELBY COUNTY...
At 248 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from Lake Purdy to near Mount Laurel to Westover, moving
northeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Leeds, Vincent, Harpersville, Westover, Fowler Lake, Vandiver, Lake
Purdy, Greystone, Mount Laurel, Brook Highland, Sterrett and Shoal
Creek.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
